FBIS4-36810 "drnes114_j_94014" FBIS-NES-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Al-'Attas, Brahimi Discuss Cease-Fire Al-'Attas, Brahimi Discuss Cease-Fire EA1306163894 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 13 Jun 94 EA1306163894 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 13 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the prime minister, yesterday met Mr. Lakhdar Brahimi, the special envoy of the UN secretary general, in the city of al-Mukalla, the capital of Hadramawt Governorate, in order to discuss with him ways of implementing UN Security Council Resolution No. 924 on a cease-fire in Yemen. The meeting was attended by brothers 'Abdallah 'Abd-al-Majid al-Asnaj, the deputy prime minister and foreign minister, and Muhsin Muhammad Bin Farid, deputy prime minister and minister of planning and development. Brother Lakhdar Brahimi, the envoy of the UN secretary general, also met representatives of the parties and of mass and creative organizations, as well as the sons of Hadramawt, who expressed their condemnation of the continuing war and fighting. They also expressed their total support for the implementation of the UN Security Council resolution calling for a cease-fire and talks between the parties. They expressed the hope that the UN envoy would be able to arrange an immediate cease-fire to prevent further destruction and bloodshed.
